Booked a reservation Friday night. They say this place is a seafood restaurant but we got the steak. Cooked perfectly and portion size was great. Service was great as well.  Dinner was priced great as well.  All in with tip and a couple of drinks bill was less than $140. If you in the area this is a great place for a nice sit down dinner.

Excellent dinner. The free garlic bread and cheese sauce  is delicious.  Our server was lovely. My wife didn't like the glass of wine she had chosen, and the server changed it with no fuss, and no charge. We had only starters. Mussels, meatballs, baked feta , and tuna tartare.  They were all first class. We couldn't decide which we liked the most. Bit disappointed they had forgotten it was my wife's birthday. But it's not a given that a restaurant has to do anything. Anyway I highly reccomend eating here.

In the land of fast casual, 11 Hanover Greek offers an extraordinary New York City dining experience, with exceptional food and service amid a delightfully captivating (see the octopus above the bar) environment.  The appropriately sized menu offers plenty of choice without overwhelming. While it features items "from the land," it's all about the seafood, much of which still twitches with life on the ice display, having arrived from destinations around the world on the same day. Order a chef creature or have the fish prepared specifically to your liking.  The appetizer selection is also robust for sharing a few small plates before the main event.  Bonus: They carry Cigar City's Jai Alai IPA!
